  "prompt": "Has California ever voted for a Republican in the general election?",
  "response": "Yes, California has historically voted for Republican candidates in presidential elections. The state was a reliable supporter of Republican presidential nominees for many decades throughout the 20th century. For example, California voted for Republican candidates in every presidential election from 1952 to 1988, with the exception of 1964 when it voted for Democrat Lyndon B. Johnson. However, in recent years, California has leaned more Democratic, voting for the Democratic presidential candidate in every election since 1992.",
